title: 2020 New Mexico House of Representatives election
2020 New Mexico House of Representatives election
added: One incumbent (a Democrat) was defeated in the general election.
Two races have not been called by independent media outlets and the outcomes could change once all votes are counted or recounts take place.
#District 27: Incumbent Democrat [[Marian Matthews]] leads Republican (and 2018 candidate) Robert Godshall by 358 votes (or 2.0%).
#District 53: Incumbent Democrat [[Willie D. Madrid]] leads Republican (and former incumbent for the district) Ricky Little by 37 votes (or 0.6%).
